<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States may provide that only their own nationals may hold the office of elected head, deputy or member of the governing college of the executive of a basic local government unit if elected to hold office for the duration of his mandate. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriik v&otilde;ib s&auml;testada, et p&otilde;hilise omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse t&auml;itevorgani juhi, juhi aset&auml;itja v&otilde;i liikme ametikohal v&otilde;ivad olla ainult nende enda kodanikud, kui need isikud valitakse ametisse kogu volituste kehtivuse ajaks. </eesti>
<inglise> The Member States may also lay down that the temporary or interim performance of the functions of a head, deputy or member of the governing college of the executive of a basic local government unit may be restricted to own nationals. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriik v&otilde;ib samuti s&auml;testada, et p&otilde;hilise omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse t&auml;itevorgani juhi, juhi aset&auml;itja v&otilde;i liikme &uuml;lesannete ajutise v&otilde;i vahepealse t&auml;itmise puhul v&otilde;idakse piirduda oma kodanikega. </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty and to general legal principles, Member States may take appropriate, necessary and proportional measures to ensure that the offices referred to in the first subparagraph can only be held and the interim functions referred to in the second subparagraph can be performed only by their own nationals. </inglise>
<eesti> Asutamislepingut ja &uuml;ldisi &otilde;igusp&otilde;him&otilde;tteid arvesse v&otilde;ttes v&otilde;ib liikmesriik v&otilde;tta asjakohaseid, vajalikke ja proportsionaalseid meetmeid, tagamaks, et esimeses l&otilde;igus nimetatud ametikohtadel olla ja teises l&otilde;igus nimetatud vahepealseid &uuml;lesandeid t&auml;ita saavad ainult nende oma kodanikud. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
