<inglise> Article 12 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 12 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Where, on 1 January 1996, in a given Member State, the proportion of citizens of the Union of voting age who reside in it but are not nationals of it exceeds 20 % of the total number of citizens of the Union residing there who are of voting age, that Member State may, by way of derogation from this Directive: </inglise>
<eesti> Kui 1. jaanuaril 1996 on liikmesriigis valimis&otilde;iguslikus vanuses ja k&otilde;nealuses riigis elavate, kuid kodakondsuseta liidu kodanike osa suurem kui 20% seal elavate valimis&otilde;iguslikus vanuses liidu kodanike koguarvust, v&otilde;ib k&otilde;nealune liikmesriik erandina k&auml;esolevast direktiivist: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) restrict the right to vote to voters within the scope of Article 3 who have resided in that Member State for a minimum period, which may not be longer than the term for which the representative council of the municipality is elected; </inglise>
<eesti> a) reserveerida valimis&otilde;iguse artikli 3 kohaselt valimis&otilde;iguslikele isikutele, kes on k&otilde;nealuses liikmesriigis elanud miinimumperioodi, mis ei tohi olla pikem kui omavalitsuse valitud esinduskogu ametiaeg; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) restrict the right to stand as a candidate to persons entitled to stand as candidates within the scope of Article 3 who have resided in that Member State for a minimum period, which may not be longer than twice the term for which the representative council of the municipality is elected; and </inglise>
<eesti> b) reserveerida kandideerimis&otilde;iguse artikli 3 kohaselt kandideerimis&otilde;iguslikele isikutele, kes on k&otilde;nealuses liikmesriigis elanud miinimumperioodi, mis ei tohi olla pikem kui omavalitsuse valitud esinduskogu kaks ametiaega; ning </eesti>
<inglise> (c) take appropriate measures with regard to the composition of lists of candidates to encourage in particular the integration of citizens of the Union, who are nationals of another Member State. </inglise>
<eesti> c) v&otilde;tta asjakohased meetmed kandidaatide nimekirjade koosseisu suhtes, et eelk&otilde;ige soodustada m&otilde;ne teise liikmesriigi kodakondsusega liidu kodanike integratsiooni. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The Kingdom of Belgium may, by way of derogation from the provisions of this Directive, apply the provisions of paragraph 1 (a) to a limited number of local government units, the list of which it shall communicate at least one year before the local government unit elections for which it intends to invoke the derogation. </inglise>
<eesti> Belgia Kuningriik v&otilde;ib erandina k&auml;esoleva direktiivi s&auml;tetest kohaldada l&otilde;ike 1 punkti a s&auml;tteid piiratud arvu omavalitsus&uuml;ksuste suhtes, kelle nimekirja ta edastab v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks aasta enne omavalitsus&uuml;ksuse valimisi, mille puhul ta kavatseb erandit rakendada. </eesti>
<inglise> 3. </inglise>
<eesti> 3. </eesti>
<inglise> Where, on 1 January 1996, the laws of a Member State prescribe that the nationals of another Member State who reside there have the right to vote for the national parliament of that State and, for that purpose, may be entered on the electoral roll of that State under exactly the same conditions as national voters, the first Member State may, by way of derogation from this Directive, refrain from applying Articles 6 to 11 in respect of such persons. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui 1. jaanuaril 1996 n&auml;evad liikmesriigi &otilde;igusaktid ette, et k&otilde;nealuses liikmesriigis elavatel teise liikmesriigi kodanikel on &otilde;igus valida selle riigi parlamenti ja et neid v&otilde;idakse selleks kanda k&otilde;nealuse riigi valijate registrisse t&auml;pselt samadel tingimustel nagu riigi kodakondsusega valijaid, v&otilde;ib esimene liikmesriik erandina k&auml;esolevast direktiivist nende kodanike puhul loobuda artiklite 6-11 kohaldamisest. </eesti>
<inglise> 4. </inglise>
<eesti> 4. </eesti>
